lead_paragraph: Making a huge move up the leader board, Briny Baird’s eight-birdie, one-bogey effort through 15 holes got him to two shots behind the leaders Bob Estes and Daniel Chopra during the suspended third round at the Ginn sur mer Classic in Port St. Lucie, Fla., yesterday. Estes and Chopra made it through 11 holes before play was halted at 6:38 p.m.
